
@startuml

' Define the classes
class Location {
  +name: String
  +id: String
  +exhibitions: List<Exhibition>
}

class Exhibition {
  +id: String
  +title: String
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date
  +coordinator: Employee
  +items: List<ExhibitionItem>
}

class Employee {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +coach: Employee
  +coachees: List<Employee>
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  +id: String
  +title: String
  +description: String
  +desiredPieces: List<Piece>
}

class Piece {
  +id: String
  +title: String
  +artist: String
  +collector: Collector
}

class Collector {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +pieces: List<Piece>
}

' Relationships
Location "1" -- "0..*" Exhibition : contains
Exhibition "1" -- "1" Employee : has coordinator
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Employee : has coach (coaching)
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Employee : is coachee of
Exhibition "1" -- "0..*" ExhibitionItem : has items
ExhibitionItem "1" -- "0..*" Piece : requests pieces from collectors
Piece "1" -- "1" Collector : belongs to collector

@enduml

### Explanation of the Classes and Relationships:

- **Location**: Represents a physical area in the museum where exhibitions can be held.
- **Exhibition**: A specific exhibition with a title, start/end dates, a coordinator, and a list of exhibition items.
- **Employee**: An employee who may have a coach or be a coach to others. Each employee may also be the coordinator of an exhibition.
- **ExhibitionItem**: A specific item that the exhibition requires, such as a painting or drawing.
- **Piece**: A specific artwork that may be sourced from a collector.
- **Collector**: A person or entity that owns one or more pieces.

### Relationships:
- A `Location` can contain multiple `Exhibitions`.
- An `Exhibition` is coordinated by one `Employee`.
- An `Employee` may have a `Coach` (a senior employee) and may have multiple `Coachees` (junior employees).
- An `Exhibition` consists of multiple `ExhibitionItems`.
- An `ExhibitionItem` may request multiple `Pieces`.
- A `Piece` is owned by a single `Collector`.

